# ---------------------------------- #
# general specifications for protein #
# ---------------------------------- #
# by default set the oxidation number of the following atoms
all H*   1
all O*  -2
all S*  -2
all N*  -3
# only HA oxidation number is set to 0 to be able to cut CA-N or CA-C bonds
all HA*  0
# oxidation numbers of terminal residues H3 and OXT are set to 0 and -1, respectively, to get consistent charge
all H3   0
all OXT -1
# carbon atoms
all C   +4
all CA   0
all CB  -2
all CG* -2   
all CD* -1
all CE* -1
all CZ* -1 
all CH* -1
# CB changes
ALA CB  -3
ILE CB  -1
VAL CB  -1
SER CB  -1
THR CB   0
CYS CB  -1
CYX CB  -1
# CG changes
ASP CG  +3
LEU CG  -1
ILE CG2 -3
ASN CG  +3
VAL CG* -3
THR CG2 -3
HID CG  +1
HIE CG  +1
HIP CG  +1
MET CG  -1
PHE CG   0
TYR CG   0
TRP CG   0
# CD changes
GLU CD  +3
LEU CD* -3
ILE CD1 -3
GLN CD  +3
HID CD2  0
HIE CD2  0
HIP CD2  0
LYS CD  -2
TRP CD*  0
# CE changes
MET CE  -2
TRP CE2 +1
HID CE1 +2
HIE CE1 +2
HIP CE1 +2
# CZ changes
ARG CZ  +4
TYR CZ  +1
# ------------------------- #
# additional specifications #
# ------------------------- #
# Cl-
Cl- Cl- -1
